text: Debovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Taptykovsky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 49 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Ufa, 5 km from Taptykovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Debovka
